A cistern has a leak that can empty it in 8 hours. An inlet pipe with capacity of 60 litters per hour is turned on .
when the leak and the inlet tap are  turned on, the cistern filled with water is emptied in 12 hours . What is the capacity of the cistern in litters

Options:

A)720
B)360
C)2880
D)1440

    Sol
   leak in 1 hr = 1/8
   both = 1/12
   pipe in hr = 1/8 - 1/12 = 1/24
   1/24 * 1/60 
      = 1/1440


2.If an inlet pipe can fill a tank in 4 hours and an outlet pipe can empty the full tank in 5 hours, 
then what is the portion of the tank filled in 1 hour if both the pipes are kept open?

Option:
A)1/20 of the tank
B)1/30 of the tank
C)1/15 of the tank
D)None of these

    Solution :
          1/4 - 1/5 = 1/20

